  "text": "The main purpose of the management algorithm is to provide the operator with advanced capabilities of organizing a robotic swarm. The algorithm was implemented on a swarm of e-puck robots [CITATION_1] . The e-puck is a differential drive robot, around 75 mm in diameter. It is shown in Figure 1a . It has eight infrared (IR) transmitters, located around its perimeter, which the robots use to communicate with surrounding robots. Their maximum communication range is limited to 15 cm, creating a fairly stable connection between the robots. The e-puck also has Bluetooth, which allows an operator to send and receive information wirelessly via a computer.",
  "correct_citation": {
